A mob has set ablaze a suspected motorcycle thief  in Makurdi, the Benue State capital. The Nation learned that the victim snatched a commercial motorcycle at gunpoint in the High Level area  and was getting away with it when the bike owner raised the alarm and residents went after  him. The residents caught up with him and a mob soon closed in. They tied up his hands, poured petrol on him and set him on fire. Police spokeswoman DSP Kate Anene confirmed the incident, but warned the people to desist from jungle justice. At press time his body was still at the scene of the incident.